cl-constant-time
================

This library was extracted from the CLPIC (Common Lisp P2P Intellectual
Property Chain) project.

Original source: src/crypto/constant-time.lisp
Extraction date: 2026-03-11

The constant-time algorithms implemented here follow NIST guidelines for
timing side-channel resistance as documented in:

- NIST SP 800-56A Rev.3: Recommendation for Pair-Wise Key-Establishment Schemes
- NIST SP 800-56B Rev.2: Recommendation for Pair-Wise Key-Establishment Using IFC
- NIST SP 800-56C Rev.2: Recommendation for Key-Derivation Methods

This is a standalone library with no external dependencies beyond ANSI Common
Lisp (with SBCL extensions for raw memory operations).
